<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>redkb – Args parsing</title><link>/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/</link><description>Recent content in Args parsing on redkb</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 08 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Argparse</title><link>/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/argparse/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/argparse/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Cyclopts</title><link>/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/cyclopts/</link><pubDate>Wed, 08 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/programming/python/argument_parsing/cyclopts/</guid><description>
&lt;h2&gt;Overview&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="overview"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#overview" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://cyclopts.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;cyclopts&lt;/code&gt;&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is a Python library that helps with building CLI/TUI applications. It is inspired by and comparable to libraries like &lt;a href="https://click.palletsprojects.com/en/stable/"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;click&lt;/code&gt;&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://github.com/google/python-fire"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;fire&lt;/code&gt;&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://typer.tiangolo.com"target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Typer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;svg class="hx:inline hx:rtl:rotate-270 hx:align-baseline" height="1em" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
&lt;path d="m9.1716 7.7574h7.0711m0 0v7.0711m0-7.0711-8.4853 8.4853" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/&gt;
&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and in fact directly compares itself to &lt;code&gt;Typer&lt;/code&gt; in a number of instances.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;cyclopts&lt;/code&gt; helps to reduce boilerplate code, and allows for flexible structuring of your code in files. It makes adding commands and &lt;code&gt;--args&lt;/code&gt; simple, and can handle some fairly complex configurations, or very simple argument parsing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the sections on the left to read more about using &lt;code&gt;cyclopts&lt;/code&gt; to build CLIs for your apps.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>